When Cantera converts cti files to xml files, it writes a temporary  
file containing python commands, and then runs python with this  
command file to do the conversion.  It seems you do not have write  
access in the directory you are trying to run the MATLAB demos from.

The easiest fix is to set environment variable TMP or TEMP. if either  
of these is set, the temporary file will be written there, and not in  
the current directory.
Or you can run the demos from a directory where you do have write  
access.

Dave


